# Direction Regularity Is Prior Art, Not A Standalone Novelty Claim

Status: `VERIFIED` with `INFERRED` consequence

The local geometry corpus already treats vorticity-direction regularity as an
existing conditional-regularity framework. The mission context explicitly names
the Constantin-Fefferman route, and the refined geometry chain says the branch
must benchmark against Constantin-Fefferman-Majda style direction coherence and
later vorticity-direction coherence work before claiming novelty.

The repository's theorem-level boundary is still headline-only. It records that
sufficiently regular vorticity direction implies regularity, but it does not
reconstruct the full hypotheses, norms, or proof details of the cited
direction-coherence literature.

The consequence is operational: a later step may not call a route new if it
only restates that sufficiently regular or coherent vorticity direction yields
regularity, or if it reaches that statement only by importing stronger
`nabla xi`-type control. To stay live, the branch would need a new
Navier-Stokes-specific bridge from localized direction coherence to full
stretching control or to a persistence mechanism that is not already absorbed
by the known criterion family.

Filed from:
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-002-exploration-001-geometry-prior-art-benchmark.md`
# Standalone Beltrami Alignment Collapses To A Fragility Screen

Status: `VERIFIED` with `INFERRED` consequence

The local record already contains the main Beltrami boundary:

- exact Beltrami alignment kills the Lamb-vector / pressure-side CZ loss;
- the effect is extremely fragile under perturbation;
- and local alignment does not by itself control the full stretching mechanism
  `S omega . omega`, especially its exterior or nonlocal part.

Therefore local Beltrami or alignment language is not a primary route for the
geometry branch. At most it remains a fragility screen or a weak hybrid
ingredient, for example when paired with concentration or anisotropy on a fixed
intense set. A route also fails the novelty benchmark if it reaches an existing
direction-coherence criterion only by importing stronger `nabla xi`-type
control under Beltrami-flavored language.

Exploration 002 sharpened the hybrid verdict as well:

- `Beltrami deficit plus concentration` is still only `weak but informative`
- `Beltrami deficit plus anisotropy` is still only `weak but informative`

Those variants do not rescue the route unless they name a full-stretching gain,
including the exterior or nonlocal contribution.

Filed from:
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-002-exploration-001-geometry-prior-art-benchmark.md`
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-002-exploration-002-geometry-tao-screen.md`
# Tube Persistence Remains Live Only As A Dynamic Or Hybrid Route

Status: `VERIFIED` with `INFERRED` consequence

The geometry planning record repeatedly separates tube coherence or persistence
from both direction regularity and Beltrami deficit. The surviving value of
this family is not descriptive tube language or one-time coherent-structure
snapshots. The local corpus does not yet contain a standalone theorem-level
tube-persistence regularity criterion, so its only live content is dynamic:

- a transport or persistence mechanism for coherent structures across scales and
  time;
- tied to a fixed scenario and localization protocol;
- and relevant to the full stretching mechanism rather than to geometry alone,
  for example by shrinking an exterior or inter-scale stretching contribution
  or the localization-evolution cost.

Without that persistence ingredient, tube language is only descriptive and does
not clear the Tao screen.

Filed from:
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-002-exploration-001-geometry-prior-art-benchmark.md`
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-002-exploration-002-geometry-tao-screen.md`
# Anchor Reconstruction Goals To A Small Source List

When the task is to reconstruct an inherited argument, anchor the goal to a
short mandatory source list.

If no dedicated prior-art packet exists yet, say explicitly that the selected
mission or planning files are being used as a benchmark memo rather than as a
complete literature reconstruction. That keeps theorem-detail gaps honest
instead of letting the report imply coverage it does not have.

In Exploration 001 this prevented broad re-derivation of pressure background and
kept the report tied to the copied mission evidence that the branch actually
depends on.

Filed from:
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-exploration-001.md`
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-002-exploration-001.md`
# Exploration Goal Design

Reusable prompt-design lessons for tightly scoped exploration runs that need to
reconstruct inherited arguments rather than re-derive background.

## Entries

- `require-an-explicit-formula-sheet-for-obstruction-branches.md`: force the
  report to pin down the live formula instead of paraphrasing the obstruction.
- `compute-exactly-which-modes-the-test-structure-kills.md`: prevent fake
  progress from quotienting out modes that were already annihilated.
- `anchor-reconstruction-goals-to-a-small-source-list.md`: keep reconstruction
  runs tied to copied mission evidence and frame thin benchmark packets
  honestly.
- `build-a-dedicated-prior-art-packet-before-benchmarking-a-literature-heavy-branch.md`:
  sharpen later novelty screens by reducing dependence on planning prose.
- `normalize-notation-and-name-the-operative-bound-up-front.md`: remove sign
  drift and force a choice between schematic and concrete inherited bounds.
- `state-nonlocal-moment-dependence-in-the-goal.md`: say up front when a branch
  depends on a remote moment problem, so local claims can be screened quickly.
- `write-forbid-novelty-claim-rules-for-prior-art-benchmarks.md`: make prior-art
  overlap operational by requiring explicit relabeling bans for each candidate
  family.
- `fix-a-provisional-stretching-representation-early-in-geometry-screens.md`:
  make geometry screens choose a provisional full-stretching representation
  before candidate triage gets too schematic.
# Meta Library Index

Methodology, goal-design patterns, and system behavior lessons for Philosopher Atlas.

## Topics

- `exploration-goal-design/`: reusable prompt-design lessons for formula-first
  obstruction reports, killed-mode accounting, notation normalization, source
  scoping, prior-art packet design, and earlier fixation of the operative
  control representation.
- `obstruction-screening/`: reusable rules for deciding whether a candidate
  actually acts on the live obstruction instead of merely restating it, with
  an added geometry-specific screen against static or Lamb-vector-only claims.

